# InquiriesManager.API

## Overview
A .NET 8 Web API for managing inquiries/contact forms, including CRUD operations and a monthly report endpoint.

## Features
- CRUD for inquiries: Name, Phone, Email, Departments[], Description
- Monthly report endpoint (calls SQL stored procedure)
- Basic unit tests
- Swagger UI for API documentation

## Build & Run
1. Clone the repo.
2. Run `dotnet restore`
3. Run `dotnet build`
4. Run `dotnet run`
5. Access Swagger at `/swagger`

## Components
- ASP.NET Core Web API
- Entity Framework Core (in-memory for demo)
- SQL stored procedure (see `StoredProcedures/MonthlyInquiriesReport.sql`)
- xUnit for tests

### Pros
- Modern .NET 8 stack
- Separation of concerns
- Easy to extend

### Cons
- Demo uses in-memory DB, not production-ready
- No real authentication

## Security
- Use HTTPS
- Validate input
- Add authentication/authorization for production

## Error Handling
- Uses standard API error responses
- Add global exception handling for production

## CORS
- Configure in `Program.cs` as needed

## Installation
- .NET 8 SDK required
- See above build/run steps

## Usage
- Use Swagger UI or any HTTP client to interact with endpoints

## Notes
- For production, connect to a real SQL DB and configure connection string.

## Using SQLite Database

This project now uses SQLite as its database provider.

